Text: Starting the game[edit | edit source].

No.2381
Connections: 
Text: When you begin the game, you will be standing in a landscape somewhere.

No.2382
Connections: 
Text: Take a moment to look around.

No.2383
Connections: 
Text: This is the general area (within 20 blocks) where you will reappear if you get killed.

No.2384
Connections: 
Text: It's a good idea to mark it immediately, by punching out an X of dirt and/or sand, then using the dirt or sand to build a pillar in the middle of that.

No.2385
Connections: 
Text: If you're standing on rock, look around for some dirt or sand to use, remember where you are, and go get it to build your pillar.

No.2386
Connections: 
Text: You can also use the Debug screen to save the coordinates of the spawnpoint for later use (see the page to learn how).

No.2387
Connections: 
Text: Tough and easy starts[edit | edit source].

No.2388
Connections: 
Text: A general note: Any time you're “looking around”, is a good time to turn your render distance to max, you can put it back afterward if it slows your game.

No.2389
Connections: 
Text: If you are standing on and surrounded by sand, you are likely in a desert biome.

No.2390
Connections: cane:20|sugar:19 sugar:19|cane:20 
Text: After marking your spawn point, head for high ground and look around for green grass and/or trees (cacti and sugar cane don't count.

No.2391
Connections: 
Text: ) Head that way to gather your wood.

No.2392
Connections: 
Text: If you can't see anything but desert, pick a random direction and head that way, occasionally going to high ground for a look around.

No.2393
Connections: 
Text: If you are on an island, completely surrounded by water as far as you can see, you are in an ocean biome.

No.2394
Connections: 
Text: This is perhaps the toughest start possible, and as such is highly discouraged for play by beginners -- given an ocean start, it's entirely reasonable to discard the world and make a new one.

No.2395
Connections: 
Text: Assuming you don't do that: If your island has no trees, you will need to swim to another island or mainland to find wood.

No.2396
Connections: 
Text: (Remember that if you die before sleeping in a bed, you will respawn on the island.

No.2397
Connections: 
Text: ) When you swim you may see squid.

No.2398
Connections: 
Text: Squid are mobs but they are not hostile.

No.2399
Connections: 
Text: Like cows, sheep, and chickens, they can't attack you (or even defend themselves), but killing them gives only ink sacs (and some XP).

No.2400
Connections: 
Text: If, looking around, you see dull,purplish land, your game just got a lot easier: you are on a mushroom biome, where monsters will not spawn (if it's connected to the mainland, congratulations, you found one of the rarest landscapes in the game).

No.2401
Connections: 
Text: Monsters can still come in from other biomes, but if you head toward the middle, you can spend the night in safety outdoors.

No.2402
Connections: 
Text: Also, with a bowl, you can get free food from the mooshrooms which live there.

No.2403
Connections: stone:25|wood:23 wood:23|stone:25 stone:25|mushroom:4 mushroom:4|stone:25 wood:23|mushroom:4 mushroom:4|wood:23 
Text: However, one thing the mushroom biome does not have, is wood—so before you go there, head for a grassy area to get some wood and stone first.

No.2404
Connections: 
Text: If, looking around, you see houses and/or farms, you are near an NPC village.

No.2405
Connections: stone:41|chest:48 chest:48|stone:41 
Text: This is a good place to live in general, if you can make a bed: the farms will solve your food worries for now, you can trade with the villagers, and if there's a blacksmith (look for a house with a stone slab roof), it will contain a chest with bonus items.

No.2406
Connections: 
Text: You can also scavenge a fair bit of wood even without trashing the place (try replacing logs with planks).

No.2407
Connections: 
Text: However, at first you'll want to avoid hanging out near there after dark, because zombies can spawn and kill the villagers.

No.2408
Connections: 
Text: You can avoid this fate by making a bed (see below), and consistently sleeping through the night until you can properly fortify the town against monsters):.

No.2409
Connections: wool:20|block:16 block:16|wool:20 
Text: If there are no sheep around, look for “lamp posts” in the village — the black block on top is wool (break it with your hand).

No.2410
Connections: 
Text: If you can't get enough wool for a bed, your best bets are (first choice) either get far away (150 blocks or so) from the village before nightfall, or (second best) to spend your first night(s) atop a really tall pillar, 40 blocks high or more (64 is even better).

No.2411
Connections: 
Text: By the second night you will hopefully have managed to find a bit of wool.

No.2412
Connections: 
Text: If you find yourself surrounded by many very large trees, and leaf blocks on the ground, then you have found yourself in a jungle biome.

No.2413
Connections: 
Text: The jungle biome is a good place to start because there are large trees everywhere, however, these can cause you to easily become lost.

No.2414
Connections: 
Text: Also, the cramped quarters can make it difficult to build there.

No.2415
Connections: 
Text: Jungle biomes are the only place to find ocelots (you'll need fish to tame them) and cocoa beans.

No.2416
Connections: 
Text: The sheer amount of leaves here can cause trouble for particularly old computers, lagging or even crashing the game; if you have an old computer and you haven't already switched to fast graphics, a jungle is good reason to do so.

No.2417
Connections: 
Text: If you find yourself surrounded by thick, short trees and dark grass, you are in a roofed forest biome.

No.2418
Connections: 
Text: These biomes are especially dangerous because the canopy of leaves can sometimes become so thick that monsters will spawn, even during the day.

No.2419
Connections: 
Text: However, this biome does provide ample supplies of wood and naturally spawning giant mushrooms which can be used for food and shelter for the night.

No.2420
Connections: 
Text: There are many other biomes in Minecraft, and to see a more in depth look at all of them, check the Biomes page.

No.2421
